## First Request

Let's verify your setup by fetching current mortgage rates. Replace `YOUR_API_KEY` with your actual key.

**Example Request**

```bash
curl -X GET "https://api.bankrate.com/v3/rates/mortgage?term=30&type=fixed" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Accept: application/json"
```

**Expected Response (200 OK)**

```json
{
  "data": {
    "rates": [
      {
        "term": "30-year",
        "type": "fixed",
        "rate": 6.875,
        "apr": 6.952,
        "last_updated": "2026-03-03T08:00:00Z"
      }
    ]
  },
  "meta": {
    "request_id": "req_abc123",
    "timestamp": "2026-03-03T14:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

::alert
---
appearance: "success"
show-icon: true
title: "You're all set."
---
If you received a 200 response, your API key is configured correctly. Head to the [API Catalog](/catalog) to explore all available endpoints.
::

## SDKs

Install one of our official client libraries to simplify integration. All SDKs include TypeScript or type definitions, automatic retries, and built-in rate limit handling.

| Language | Install | Version |
|----------|---------|---------|
| Node.js | `npm install @bankrate/sdk` | v3.2.1 |
| Python | `pip install bankrate-sdk` | v3.2.0 |
| Go | `go get github.com/bankrate/sdk-go` | v3.1.0 |
| Ruby | `gem install bankrate-sdk` | v2.8.0 |

